<h3 id="mcetoc_1jkudj88eem">Project Brief</h3>
<blockquote>
<p>a guy named bob the ninja tries to go to the end of  the course</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<h3>Define</h3>
<h3 id="mcetoc_1jkudkcahet"></h3>
<p class="msg--highlight msg msg--info"><em>Who is this for? What problem does it solve? What are the constraints?</em></p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li><strong><span style="color: #0097a7;">Who:</span></strong> This project is designed for scratchers who are curious about platformer games.</li>
<li><span style="color: #2dc26b;"><strong><span style="color: #0097a7;">What:</span></strong></span> My main challenge was to get the code right and turn it into reality.</li>
<li><strong><span style="color: #2dc26b;"><span style="color: #0097a7;">Constraints:</span> </span></strong>The user has to press the arrow keys so that they can move the main character. This makes sure the user can play.</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 id="mcetoc_1jkudj88eeo">Explore &amp; Ideate</h3>
<p class="msg msg--info"><em>What ideas did you consider before choosing a direction?</em></p>
<ul>
<li><strong><span style="color: #0097a7;">Brainstorming: </span></strong>I started by thinking of characters and sketching a plan for how it would look on the screen.</li>
<li><strong><span style="color: #0097a7;">The layout</span></strong>: I decided that the most important part of the screen would be bob because because he is the thing that moves.</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3>Logic Design</h3>
<h3 id="mcetoc_1jkudj88eep"></h3>
<p class="msg msg--info"><em>How did you plan the structure before building?</em></p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #0097a7;">Logic:</span></strong> I planned for bob to move whenever the user used the arrow keys                                                                                                    (bob)</p>
